message.content: cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.CC. The paper discusses machine learning and natural language processing techniques for playing Quizbowl, which involves answering trivia questions. This suggests that the paper could belong to several arXiv CS sub-categories, including cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.CC (Computational Complexity). Among these, cs.CL is the most likely category, as it specifically deals with natural language processing and is the most relevant to the paper's focus on question answering. The other categories are also relevant, as they involve machine learning and information retrieval techniques that could be applied to Quizbowl.
